template.value:
You are an expert policy architect. Generate publication-ready website policies for the following product.

Product: {product_name}
Description: {product_description}
Jurisdictions: {jurisdictions}
Policies needed: {policy_types}
Sub-processors: {sub_processors}
Company details: {company_details}

Return ONLY a valid JSON object with this structure:
{{
  "product_name": "{product_name}",
  "generated_at": "<ISO date>",
  "jurisdictions": ["list of covered jurisdictions"],
  "policies": {{
    "privacy_policy": {{
      "title": "Privacy Policy",
      "effective_date": "<date>",
      "content": "<full markdown policy text>",
      "word_count": <integer>,
      "compliance_flags": ["DPDP 2023", "GDPR", "CCPA"]
    }},
    "terms_of_service": {{
      "title": "Terms of Service",
      "effective_date": "<date>",
      "content": "<full markdown policy text>",
      "word_count": <integer>
    }},
    "cookie_policy": {{
      "title": "Cookie Policy",
      "effective_date": "<date>",
      "content": "<full markdown policy text>",
      "word_count": <integer>
    }}
  }},
  "sub_processors_covered": ["list of sub-processors mentioned in policies"],
  "missing_information": ["list of details needed to improve the policies"],
  "legal_disclaimer": "These policies were AI-generated and should be reviewed by qualified legal counsel before publication."
}}

Important rules:
- Only generate policy types listed in: {policy_types}
- For India: reference DPDP Act 2023, include Data Fiduciary obligations
- For EU: include GDPR lawful basis, data subject rights, DPA contact
- For US: include CCPA opt-out rights if applicable
- Never invent sub-processors not listed — use only: {sub_processors}
- If company_details are empty, use placeholder text clearly marked [FILL IN]
- Return ONLY the JSON. No markdown fences. No explanation.
